h3. Summary

When saving a page, the following error occurs:

{panel}
Oops - an error has occurred System Error

Cause
java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException
    at sun.reflect.NativeMethodAccessorImpl.invoke0(Native Method)

caused by: java.lang.StackOverflowError
    at org.apache.xerces.dom.ElementImpl.synchronizeData(Unknown Source)
{panel}

h3. Expected Results

The page is able to be saved, without this exception, after an edit.

h3. Actual Results

 If you go to *... >> View Storage Format*, the page will contain a lot of tags that are unnecessary and, in some cases, these tags aren't closed.

{code:xml}
<span style="color: rgb(0,0,0);"><span style="color: rgb(0,0,0);"><span style="color: rgb(0,0,0);"><span style="color: rgb(0,0,0);"><span style="color: rgb(0,0,0);"><span style="color: rgb(0,0,0);"><span style="color: rgb(0,0,0);"> <span style="color: rgb(0,0,0);"> <span> <span> <span> <span> <span> <span> <span> <span> <span>
{code}

h3.Workaround
# Copy the content of the page with error;
# Create a new page;
# On the new page editor, paste the content;
# Save.

h3. Summary

Anonymous users are still able to search for the user avatar name (which have a username in the name) in the search box, even after deleting users avatars from Confluence database and performing reindex and cleaning the cache. The profile picture is deleted, but not its reference.

h3. Steps to Reproduce

# Backup your Confluence database;
# Stop your Confluence instance;
# On the database, run the following query:

{code:sql}
SELECT string_val FROM os_propertyentry WHERE entity_key = 'confluence.user.profile.picture';
{code}

This query will return all your *user avatars names* in the database, including the ones where the file name is different than "user-avatar".

# To remove the avatars with the username on it, run the following query:

{code:sql}
DELETE FROM os_propertyentry
WHERE string_val <> 'user-avatar';
{code}

# Start your Confluence instance;
# Rebuild the index;
# Clean the cache;
# Restart your Confluence instance.


h3. Expected Results

When using the search box, the user should not be able to see the user-avatar reference, already deleted, on the results.

h3. Actual Results

The user is able to see the reference to the user profile pictures in the search box result.
 
h3. Notes
The picture is deleted from the user's profile, but its reference remains in Confluence.

h3.Workaround
N/A
